### TaskMaster API examples
### Use with the VS Code "REST Client" extension, or translate to curl.
### Run requests top to bottom; copy the token from the register/login response.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@token = PASTE_YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

### 1. Register
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "alice",
  "email": "alice@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "fullName": "Alice Smith"
}

### 2. Login (returns a JWT)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "usernameOrEmail": "alice",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 3. Get my profile
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 4. Update my profile
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/users/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "fullName": "Alice S.", "bio": "Backend learner" }

### 5. Create a team
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/teams
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "name": "Platform Team", "description": "Core backend work" }

### 6. Create a task
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/tasks
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Implement login endpoint",
  "description": "Add JWT-based auth",
  "dueDate": "2026-07-01",
  "priority": "HIGH"
}

### 7. List tasks with filters, search and sorting
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/tasks?status=OPEN&priority=HIGH&search=login&sort=dueDate,asc&page=0&size=20
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 8. Mark a task completed (replace 1 with the task id)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/tasks/1/status
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "status": "COMPLETED" }

### 9. Assign a task (replace ids)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/tasks/1/assign
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "assigneeId": 2 }

### 10. Add a comment
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/tasks/1/comments
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "content": "Started working on this." }

### 11. Upload an attachment (multipart)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/tasks/1/attachments
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----boundary

------boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="notes.txt"
Content-Type: text/plain

Some file content here
------boundary--

### 12. Real-time notification stream (Server-Sent Events)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/notifications/stream
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 13. AI: generate a task description (requires AI enabled)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/ai/generate-description
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "title": "Set up CI pipeline", "keywords": "github actions, tests, build" }

### 14. Logout (revokes the token)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
